<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 2:50PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN BEDFORD AND
SOUTHWESTERN FULTON COUNTIES THROUGH 315 PM EDT...
At 249 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Breezewood, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clearville, Needmore, Barnes Gap, Inglesmith and Locust Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
